Vice President Pence spoke about the efforts being made by federal, state, and local governments to provide resources and support for rescue and recovery in the aftermath of Hurricane Harvey. He mentioned that the rescue operation is the main focus at the moment, but once the flood waters subside, the work of recovery will begin. Pence praised the efforts of Governor Abbott of Texas, local first responders, and the volunteer effort that is helping those affected by the storm. He also emphasized the importance of caution and following the guidance of local emergency management officials. Pence mentioned that a significant number of Americans may be eligible for disaster assistance and encouraged them to register on DisasterAssistance.gov. He also highlighted the unity, self-reliance, and compassion displayed by Americans in response to the hurricane.